q-calendar/value.description: v-model; When set as `YYYY-mm-dd`, the calendar will display the current view on this date. If empty, then it will be changed to the current date which will be emitted

q-calendar/view.description: The type of calendar view to be displayed

q-calendar/dark.description: Places a calendar in dark mode

q-calendar/bordered.description: Places a border around the calendar

q-calendar/now.description: This is the currently displayed date (highlighted). If not set, then the current date is used

q-calendar/weekdays.description: This is the days of the week and in which order they are displayed. If you want Monday as the first day of the week, you would use [1,2,3,4,5,6,0]. If you want a 5-day work week you would use [1,2,3,4,5]

q-calendar/no-active-date.description: This controls whether the `q-active-date` css class is set when a user clicks on a date label (button)

q-calendar/disabled-days.description: An array of string dates in the form `YYYY-mm-dd` that will be disabled

q-calendar/disabled-before.description: A date in the form `YYYY-mm-dd` where all dates before, and including, will be disabled

q-calendar/disabled-after.description: A date in the form `YYYY-mm-dd` where all dates after, and including, will be disabled

q-calendar/locale.description: Used to change the locale of the calendar

q-calendar/max-days.description: The number of days to be displayed. Applicable only for custom-interval, scheduler and agenda views

q-calendar/color.description: This is the color used current day (now) highlighting. It can be from the from the [Quasar Color Palette](https://quasar.dev/style/color-palette), CSS named color or a CSS color (#, rgb, rgba, hls, etc)

q-calendar/theme.description: Object containing keys and values that overrides the calendar's color properties. See online demo for format of a theme

q-calendar/short-weekday-label.description: Displays the weekday label in short format. For instance, 'Monday' would become 'Mon'

q-calendar/transition-prev.description: When animated property is true, transition to use for previous calendar view

q-calendar/transition-next.description: When animated property is true, transition to use for next calendar view

q-calendar/drag-over-func.description: The function to handle dragover events

q-calendar/drop-func.description: The function to handle drop events

q-calendar/no-scroll.description: Turns off the internal scrollbar. Useful if you want to handle your own scrolling

q-calendar/column-header-before.description: Turns on the column-header-before scoped slot

q-calendar/column-header-after.description: Turns on the column-header-after scoped slot

q-calendar/column-count.description: Applicable only for day view. Show the same day x number of times in columns. Scoped slots get this data as index in passed object

q-calendar/column-index-start.description: Applicable only for day view. This is the starting index. This allows you to create a paging system (next/prev) when using column-count property

q-calendar/interval-height.description: The maximum height in pixels for the interval height

q-calendar/interval-style.description: Gets called to provide custom styling of an interval

q-calendar/interval-minutes.description: The number of minutes in an interval

q-calendar/interval-count.description: The number intervals to use. If interval-minutes is set to 30 then you would set interval count to 48 â€“ double that of regular

q-calendar/day-height.description: The maximum height in pixels for the day height. Using 0 will make the rows variable height based on content.

q-calendar/day-padding.description: Overrides the padding to be used for a day element. You can use any CSS padding format

q-calendar/day-style.description: Gets called to provide custom styling of a day

q-calendar/day-class.description: Gets called to provide custom styling (via classes) of a day

q-calendar/min-weeks.description: The minimum number of weeks to be displayed

q-calendar/short-month-label.description: Makes the month label short. January becomes Jan...

q-calendar/no-default-header-btn.description: Do not display the day button in the header

q-calendar/no-default-header-text.description: Do not display the day text in the header

q-calendar/show-month-label.description: Shows the month label - this occurs on the 1st of the month

q-calendar/show-day-of-year-label.description: Show the say of the year - this occurs in the top right of each day element. If show-month-label is true, then that day is skipped

q-calendar/resources.description: An array of objects with a single key of label. You can add other keys if you like, which will be passed back on the appropriate scoped slots

q-calendar/resource-height.description: The maximum height in pixels for the resource height

q-calendar/resource-width.description: The maximum width in pixels for the resource width

q-calendar/resource-style.description: Gets called to provide custom styling of a resource

q-calendar/selected-start-end-dates.description: An array of two dates in format `YYYY-mm-dd` for selection purposes

q-calendar/selected-dates.description: An array of string dates in the form `YYYY-mm-dd` that will be selected

q-calendar/mini-mode.description: When `true` puts the calendar into mini-mode. When `auto`, then the property `breakpoint` is used to determine when the calendar will be put into mini-mode

q-calendar/breakpoint.description: This property is used when `mini-mode` is set with `auto`

q-calendar/month-label-size.description: This property is used change the size of the month label button. This property is ignored when `mini-mode` is set to true

q-calendar/left-column-options.description: An array of objects used to add columns to the left side of the agenda. Each object must have an id and label key or define the id object key using the `column-options-id` and the label using the `column-options-label` properties. The value of the id should be unique for each object. The object is passed to slots

q-calendar/right-column-options.description: An array of objects used to add columns to the right side of the agenda. Each object must have an id and label key or define the id object key using the `column-options-id` and the label using the `column-options-label` properties. The value of the id should be unique for each object. The object is passed to slots

q-calendar/column-options-id.description: The key in the object to use for `left-column-options` or `right-column-options` properties to define the id, otherwise `id` will be used

q-calendar/column-options-label.description: The key in the object to use for `left-column-options` or `right-column-options` properties to define the label, otherwise `label` will be used
